-- At Least Six Killed as Bangladesh Garment Factory Catches Fire
-- B y   A r u n   D e v n a t h
-- 2013-01-26T12:37:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-26/at-least-six-killed-as-bangladesh-garment-factory-catches-fire.html
At least six workers were killed
after a fire swept through a Dhaka-based garment factory,
according to the Bangladesh Fire Service and Civil Defence.  The employees of Smart Export Garments Ltd. died either
after jumping out of windows or in a stampede, Abdul Halim, a
deputy assistant director of the Fire Service, said in a
telephone interview from Dhaka.  More than 300 workers were at the factory, Major Mohammad
Mahbub, director of the Fire Serviceâ€™s operations, told
reporters. None was burnt to death, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
